\" href=\"http://forum.anmari.com/topic.php?id=442\" target=\"_blank\">&#8216;criteria&#8217; number for his member list</a>, and what others may call a scoreboard ranking, top 10 chart listing etc&#8230;..</p>\n<p>Basically we want to show the row or list number as displayed.   Some other field is used to determine the sort order.   Define the sort order in your normal list configuration.</p>\n<p>Basically the formatting function will add one as each user is displayed.</p>\n<p>Version 1.1 allows the ranking to work for more than one page.  It checks which page was requested and how many rows per page are being displayed.  Then starts the ranking count appropriately, and increments from there.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-3601\" alt=\"ranked users\" src=\"http://wpusersplugin.com/wpusers/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/ranking.jpg\" width=\"211\" height=\"156\" /></p>\n<p>The add-on is a very simple little example plugin.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>It allows a ranking field to be displayed.  Use &#8220;find fields&#8221; to bring it up after plugin activation.</li>\n<li>Then configure your list, scroll down till you see the ranking field.  Add a number to the display column to say which column it should display in.</li>\n<li>Save</li>\n<li>Rebuild cache.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The downloads will be accessible to logged in users who have access to amr-users-plus:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\'http://wpusersplugin.com/wpusers/?ym_download_id=25\' title=\'amr users ranking 1.1\' >amr users ranking 1.1</a> &#8211; Ranking over multiple pages.</li>\n<li><a href=\'http://wpusersplugin.com/wpusers/?ym_download_id=24\' title=\'amr users ranking 1.0\' >amr users ranking 1.0</a> &#8211; Single Page ranking</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"http://wpusersplugin.